cvpiaHabitat
  • Reference

Sutter Bypass Flow to Floodplain Habitat Area Relationship

A dataset containing the floodplain habitat area in acres as a function of flow in cubic feet per second

sutter_bypass_floodplain

Format

dataframe with 41 rows and 5 variables:

flow_cfs

integer flow value in cubic feet per second

Sutter Bypass 1

floodplain acreage in the Sutter Bypass, to Moulton Weir

Sutter Bypass 2

floodplain acreage in the Sutter Bypass, to Colusa Weir

Sutter Bypass 3

floodplain acreage in the Sutter Bypass, to Tisdale Weir

Sutter Bypass 4

floodplain acreage in the Sutter Bypass below Tisdale Weir

Source

Central Valley Floodplain Evaluation and Delineation (CVFED) HEC-RAS hydraulic model refined for use in the NOAA-NMFS Winter Run Chinook Salmon life cycle model

Details

Habitat estimates are freom the Central Valley Floodplain Evaluation and Delineation (CVFED) HEC-RAS hydraulic model refined for use in the NOAA-NMFS Winter Run Chinook Salmon life cycle model.

High quality defined by:

Channel depth > 0.2 m and < 1.5 m

Velocity <= 0.15 m/s
